n': 'numpy uniform distribution U(0,1)', 'label_smoothing_alpha': '0.1'}}, 'deadline': '2025-11-21 12:00:00', 'weighting': '50%', 'project_plan': [{'step': 'Setup and familiarization with EMNIST dataset and Coursework 1 branch', 'target_date': '2025-11-10', 'estimated_hours': 2}, {'step': 'Task 1: Problem identification - Baseline hyperparameter search and network width/depth experiments', 'target_date': '2025-11-12', 'estimated_hours': 15}, {'step': 'Task 2: Implementation of regularization techniques - DropoutLayer, L1Penalty, L2Penalty classes', 'target_date': '2025-11-14', 'estimated_hours': 10}, {'step': 'Implementation of L1L2MixPenalty and label smoothing function', 'target_date': '2025-11-15', 'estimated_hours': 5}, {'step': 'Running unit tests and generating test outputs file', 'target_date': '2025-11-16', 'estimated_hours': 2}, {'step': 'Task 2: EMNIST experiments with different regularization methods and hyperparameter tuning', 'target_date': '2025-11-18', 'estimated_hours': 25}, {'step': 'Custom activation function investigation and analysis', 'target_date': '2025-11-19', 'estimated_hours': 8}, {'step': 'Task 3: Writing conclusions and literature contextualization', 'target_date': '2025-11-20', 'estimated_hours': 6}, {'step': 'Report compilation, LaTeX formatting, and final review', 'target_date': '2025-11-21', 'estimated_hours': 5}], 'description_short': 'This coursework involves studying classification of handwritten digit images using neural networks on the EMNIST Balanced dataset. Students must identify and discuss a fundamental problem in machine learning (overfitting), then implement different methods to combat this problem including Dropout, L1Penalty, L2Penalty, and label smoothing. The work includes empirical and theoretical comparison of these approaches, followed by presenting conclusions contextualized in literature. The project builds on Coursework 1 setup and requires a comprehensive report with experimental results.'}, 'created_at': '2025-11-24T10:21:40.865959+00:00', 'updated_at': None, 'deadline': '2026-01-15T00:00:00+00:00'}]]
