 network (3 hidden layers, 128 units) using Dropout, L1/L2 penalties, label smoothing, and combined L1+L2 techniques. Generate test outputs and analyze results', 'target_date': '2025-11-20', 'time_estimate': '20 hours'}, {'step': 'Custom activation function analysis', 'description': 'Investigate performance problems with provided CustomActivationLayer setup and relate findings to regularization methods', 'target_date': '2025-11-21', 'time_estimate': '5 hours'}, {'step': 'Task 3: Conclusions and literature review', 'description': 'Write comprehensive conclusions summarizing work, drawing conclusions, and relating findings to overall literature', 'target_date': '2025-11-21', 'time_estimate': '8 hours'}, {'step': 'Report compilation and submission', 'description': 'Compile final report using LaTeX template, include all figures and tables, generate PDF, and prepare submission zip file', 'target_date': '2025-11-21', 'time_estimate': '7 hours'}], 'description_short': 'This coursework focuses on studying the classification of handwritten digits using neural networks with the EMNIST Balanced dataset. Students must identify and discuss fundamental problems in machine learning (overfitting), implement different methods to combat these problems, and compare these methods empirically and theoretically. The coursework is structured into three tasks: problem identification through baseline experiments, implementing and testing regularization techniques (Dropout, L1/L2 penalties, label smoothing), and drawing conclusions contextualized in literature. The main deliverable is a comprehensive report submitted as a PDF along with modified code.'}, 'created_at': '2025-11-24T10:48:19.124557+00:00', 'updated_at': None, 'deadline': '2026-01-14T00:00:00+00:00'}]]
