[2025-11-25 00:54:35,973;INFO;projects;[DELETE PROJECT] Project deleted: [{'id': '9b38fc68-a7a3-4966-a194-59d9ba736871', 'user_id': 'bc77eb3d-e3ba-4a2f-b5dd-a2543630a3ff', 'title': 'MLP Project', 'description': 'This is a description', 'spec_path': '9b38fc68-a7a3-4966-a194-59d9ba736871/MLP2025_26_CW2_Spec.pdf', 'summary_json': {'extra': {'github_url': 'https://github.com/MLPgithub', 'late_policy': 'You may submit more than once up until the submission deadline. All submissions are timestamped automatically. If you submit anything before the deadline, you may not resubmit after the deadline. If you do not submit anything before the deadline, you may submit exactly once after the deadline up to a maximum of 7 calendar days.', 'other_notes': 'Use dropout uniform distribution U(0,1) to pass the unit tests. Label smoothing parameter α must be set to 0.1. Dropout inclusion probability should be in range (0,1), e.g., 0.5. Penalty coefficient should be manually selected float value, e.g., 0.001, usually in range 0.1-0.00001. Use validation performance for model selection and report test performance of best model. Run each network for 100 epochs using Adam optimizer with hyperparameters provided in template.', 'extension_policy': 'Extension requests must be submitted according to instructions on the webpage at https://informatics.ed.ac.uk/taught-students/all-students/your-studies/late-coursework-extension-requests. Do not email any course staff directly about extension requests.'}, 'tasks': [{'id': '854013f1-1bf5-47c3-9780-a3fa65022e1e', 'task': 'Identify fundamental overfitting problem in neural networks and set up baseline system', 'source_sentence': 'The first part of this coursework will concern the identification and discussion of a fundamental problem in machine learning, as shown in Figure 1.'}, {'id': '1088e8ae-8108-435c-90f7-824f563bc987', 'task': 'Investigate overfitting in wider and deeper neural networks by varying hidden units and layers', 'source_sentence': 'Following this preliminary discussion, you will further investigate this problem in wider and deeper neural networks, study it in terms of network width and depth.'}, {'id': 'a68edc8b-be4b-4035-93b3-e92ad8a2fe1b', 'task': 'Implement different methods to combat the overfitting problem', 'source_sentence': 'The second part involves implementing different methods to combat the problem identified in Task 1 and then comparing these methods empirically and theoretically.'}, {'id': '8fb4c837-185a-432d-8bfe-2164fb07b117', 'task': 'Train various 1-hidden layer networks with 32, 64, and 128 ReLU hidden units on EMNIST', 'source_sentence': 'Initially you will train various 1-hidden layer networks by using either 32, 64 and 128 ReLU hidden units per layer on EMNIST.'}, {'id': 'c8e1a52b-8948-4685-814a-b5c83e8c799e', 'task': 'Train neural networks with 1, 2, 3 hidden layers using 128 ReLU hidden units per layer', 'source_sentence': 'Here you will train various neural networks by using either 1,2,3 hidden layers with 128 ReLU hidden units per layer on EMNIST.'}, {'id': 'e306dfff-1a79-4c75-999c-4570f9043d72', 'task': 'Implement DropoutLayer in mlp.layers module with fprop and bprop methods', 'source_sentence': 'Implement the Dropout class in the DropoutLayer of the mlp.layers module. You need to implement fprop and bprop methods for this class.'}, {'id': 'a534ed97-4edb-4ed1-8532-88133614622a', 'task': 'Implement L1Penalty and L2Penalty classes in mlp.penalties module', 'source_sentence': 'Implement the L1Penalty and L2Penalty class in the L1Penalty and L2Penalty of the mlp.penalties module. You need to implement __call__ and grad methods for this class.'}, {'id': 'a077f3d8-0074-4a6e-b5a7-68ca096b7d35', 'task': 'Implement L1L2MixPenalty combining L1 and L2 penalties into one loss function', 'source_sentence': 'Here you will also need to implement a new weight penalty technique in the mlp.penalties module: L1L2MixPenalty.'}, {'id': '2bc5e42c-9eb4-4972-a0be-01825ea25e25', 'task': 'Implement label smoothing function in EMNISTDataProvider class', 'source_sentence': 'To implement the label smoothing function, fill in label_smoothing function in EMNISTDataProvider class of data_providers.py and identify when this function is called.'}, {'id': '118f12dc-1ff1-4f70-a741-ee5fa46b1bcc', 'task': 'Run experiments with baseline network using DropoutLayer, L1Penalty, or L2Penalty', 'source_sentence': 'Here you should modify your baseline network to one that uses DropoutLayer, L1Penalty, or L2Penalty and train a model for each case.'}, {'id': '078655d6-c675-4d35-8919-fe1cbf015952', 'task': 'Run experiment with baseline setup plus label smoothing', 'source_sentence': 'You will also run one experiment with the baseline setup plus label smoothing, using no other regularization techniques.'}, {'id': '27ce514c-f8eb-4e92-96f7-d58f30807382', 'task': 'Investigate and explain performance problems with custom activation layer', 'source_sentence': 'You will finally investigate and explain the performance problems with a provided model setup and experiment run, that uses a custom activation layer.'}, {'id': 'd617e182-ebfc-440a-bad4-ab1d6ae20d1b', 'task': 'Summarise work, draw conclusions, and relate them to the overall literature', 'source_sentence': 'In this section, you will summarise your work, draw conclusions, and relate them to the overall literature.'}], 'datasets': [{'name': 'EMNIST Balanced dataset', 'details': 'Extended MNIST dataset with 47 labels (10 digits, 26 lowercase letters, 26 uppercase letters with 15 merged due to confusion between cases). Images are 28x28 dimension, extracted from NIST Special Database 19 using same conversion process as MNIST. Training set has about twice the number of examples as MNIST.'}], 'deadline': '2025-11-21T12:00:00', 'weighting': '50%', 'deliverables': [{'name': 'PDF report', 'details': 'Completed report as PDF file renamed as Sxxxxxx_report.pdf using the provided template'}, {'name': 'MLP code', 'details': 'Local version of mlp code including any changes to the provided .py files'}, {'name': 'Test outputs file', 'details': 'Generated file xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy created by running the provided script'}, {'name': 'Jupyter notebook', 'details': 'Coursework_1.ipynb notebook containing experiment setup'}], 'description_long': 'This coursework uses the EMNIST (Extended MNIST) Balanced dataset, which extends the well-known MNIST dataset by including handwritten letters (both upper and lowercase) as well as handwritten digits. The 47-label dataset contains 10 digits and merged upper/lowercase versions of certain confusing letters. The coursework is structured into three main tasks: problem identification through baseline experiments, research investigation into regularization techniques, and literature contextualization in the conclusions. Students implement various neural network components and conduct experiments to study network width and depth effects on overfitting.', 'methods_required': ['Neural networks with ReLU activation', 'Adam optimizer', 'Dropout technique', 'L1 weight penalty', 'L2 weight penalty', 'L1L2MixPenalty (combined L1 and L2 regularization)', 'Label smoothing', 'Custom activation function', 'Cross-entropy error function'], 'description_short': 'This coursework involves studying the classification of handwritten digits using neural networks on the EMNIST Balanced dataset. Students first identify and discuss overfitting problems in machine learning models through training and validation curves. The project then involves implementing various methods to combat overfitting, including Dropout, weight penalties (L1, L2, and a proposed L1+L2 combination), and label smoothing techniques. Students conduct empirical and theoretical comparisons of these methods, evaluate their effects on model performance, and investigate custom activation functions. The final deliverable is a comprehensive report that contextualizes findings within the broader literature.', 'evaluation_metrics': ['Training accuracy', 'Validation accuracy', 'Training error', 'Validation error', 'Test performance'], 'submission_requirements': ['Submit as zip file Sxxxxxx.zip containing all required files', 'PDF report must be renamed as Sxxxxxx_report.pdf', 'Include test outputs file xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy', 'Include local version of mlp code with changes to .py files', 'Include Coursework_1.ipynb notebook', 'Use specific zip command provided: zip -r Sxxxxxx.zip mlp/ Coursework_1.ipynb Sxxxxxx_report.pdf xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy', 'Verify contents using unzip -l command before submission', 'File size should be few MBs only and must not contain model weights', 'Submit through the Learn course webpage under Assessment section']}, 'created_at': '2025-11-25T00:54:26.929537+00:00', 'updated_at': None, 'deadline': '2026-01-14T00:00:00+00:00'}]]
