[2025-11-25 00:54:38,415;INFO;projects;[DELETE PROJECT] Project deleted: [{'id': '21b6aa2b-6051-4981-a9d0-ca51d6889ba9', 'user_id': 'bc77eb3d-e3ba-4a2f-b5dd-a2543630a3ff', 'title': 'MLP Project', 'description': 'This is a description', 'spec_path': '21b6aa2b-6051-4981-a9d0-ca51d6889ba9/MLP2025_26_CW2_Spec.pdf', 'summary_json': {'extra': {'github_url': 'https://github.com', 'late_policy': 'You may submit more than once up until the submission deadline. If you do not submit anything before the deadline, you may submit exactly once after the deadline up to a maximum of 7 calendar days.', 'other_notes': 'The coursework is identical to coursework 1, with only the marking clarified to be counting for 50% of the final grade. Continue working from the coursework1 branch without creating a new branch or editing filenames.', 'extension_policy': 'Extension requests must follow the instructions on the webpage https://informatics.ed.ac.uk/taught-students/all-students/your-studies/late-coursework-extension-requests Do not email any course staff directly about extension requests.'}, 'tasks': [{'id': '473edf07-3281-4772-90a0-d3a6dd5845c0', 'task': 'Implement DropoutLayer class in mlp.layers module with fprop and bprop methods using uniform distribution U(0,1)', 'source_sentence': "1. Implement the Dropout class in the DropoutLayer of the mlp.layers module. You need to implement fprop and bprop methods for this class. Please note that the solution uses the original dropout formulation (i.e. scale the hidden unit activations by inclusion probability p in the final network for compensating missing units). The sample distribution to be used for Dropout implementation is numpy's uniform distribution, U(0,1) to pass the unit tests."}, {'id': 'b6f37ce2-9d45-4be9-80a9-a077d7c21ab5', 'task': 'Implement L1Penalty and L2Penalty classes in mlp.penalties module with __call__ and grad methods', 'source_sentence': '2. Implement the L1Penalty and L2Penalty class in the L1Penalty and L2Penalty of the mlp.penalties module. You need to implement __call__ and grad methods for this class. After defining these functions, they can be provided as a parameter, weights_penalty, biases_penalty in the AffineLayer class while creating the multi-layer neural network.'}, {'id': '86378036-9c85-44ce-b4d6-b1cef3eac326', 'task': 'Fill in label_smoothing function in EMNISTDataProvider class with α = 0.1', 'source_sentence': '5. To implement the label smoothing function, fill in label_smoothing function in EMNISTDataProvider class of data_providers.py and identify when this function is called. This function must replace the hard target 0 labels and 1 labels with α and 1−α respectively. α must be set to 0.1.'}, {'id': '2cd54bfb-d9b8-46e1-97e5-7cf788b5c3ef', 'task': 'Implement L1L2MixPenalty combining L1 and L2 penalties in mlp.penalties module', 'source_sentence': '6. Implement your proposed L1 and L2 combined weight penalty, as the L1L2MixPenalty in the mlp.penalties module.'}, {'id': 'f6db2658-b040-4056-a380-4102f43cbfea', 'task': 'Identify the fundamental problem shown in Figure 1 as overfitting', 'source_sentence': 'Figure 1 shows the training and validation error curves in Figure 1a and also training and validation accuracies in Figure 1b for a model with 2 hidden layers with ReLU trained on the EMNIST dataset by using cross-entropy error function. We first identify and discuss the problem shown by the curves in Figure 1 as overfitting, and briefly discuss potential solutions in this section for overcoming this problem.'}, {'id': 'b56ed279-0199-4b9e-b974-06498f181fbb', 'task': 'Train various 1-hidden layer networks with 32, 64, and 128 ReLU hidden units on EMNIST using Adam optimizer for 100 epochs', 'source_sentence': 'Varying number of hidden units. Initially you will train various 1-hidden layer networks by using either 32, 64 and 128 ReLU hidden units per layer on EMNIST. Note that 1-hidden layer network contains two layers, one mapping input units to hidden units and another one mapping hidden units to output units. Make sure you use Adam optimiser with the hyper-parameters provided in the template and train each network for 100 epochs.'}, {'id': '4ec5b215-3188-4362-a3df-d9bc5669e68f', 'task': 'Train various neural networks using 1, 2, 3 hidden layers with 128 ReLU hidden units per layer on EMNIST using Adam optimizer for 100 epochs', 'source_sentence': 'Varying number of layers. Here you will train various neural networks by using either 1, 2, 3 hidden layers with 128 ReLU hidden units per layer on EMNIST. Make sure that you use Adam optimiser with the hyper-parameters provided in the template and train each network for 100 epochs.'}, {'id': '8e8f3789-9415-4b4d-9455-9ac61f06798e', 'task': 'Run EMNIST experiments with baseline network containing 3 hidden layers and 128 hidden units with ReLU activation function using Adam optimiser with learning rate 10^-4', 'source_sentence': 'For the experiments, your baseline network should contain 3 hidden layers and 128 hidden units with ReLU activation function. You should use the Adam optimiser with a learning rate of 10−4 as specified in the template.'}, {'id': '27fb67cf-620f-4e91-a0f6-c96712c635f9', 'task': 'Generate test outputs file by running the provided script with student ID number', 'source_sentence': '4. Automatically create test outputs xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy, by running the provided program scripts/generate_regularization_layer_test_outputs.py which uses your code for the previously mentioned layers to run your fprop, bprop, __call__ and grad methods where necessary for each layer on a unique test vector generated using your student ID number.'}], 'datasets': [{'name': 'EMNIST Balanced dataset', 'details': 'Extended MNIST dataset with 47 labels including handwritten digits, lowercase and uppercase letters with merged labels for confusing case-discrimination letters'}], 'deadline': '2025-11-21T12:00:00', 'weighting': '50% of final grade', 'deliverables': [{'name': 'Report as PDF file', 'details': 'The main deliverable is a report using a template available on the github'}, {'name': 'Local version of mlp code', 'details': 'Including any changes made to the provided .py files'}, {'name': 'Test outputs file', 'details': 'xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy generated by running the provided program script'}, {'name': 'Zip file', 'details': 'Sxxxxxx.zip containing all required files for submission'}], 'description_long': 'The coursework uses an extended version of the MNIST database, the EMNIST Balanced dataset, which extends MNIST by including images of handwritten letters (upper and lowercase) as well as handwritten digits. Both EMNIST and MNIST are extracted from the same underlying dataset, referred to as NIST Special Database 19, using the same conversion process resulting in centred images of dimension 28×28. There are 62 potential classes for EMNIST (10 digits, 26 lowercase letters, and 26 uppercase letters), but a reduced label set of 47 different labels is used, merging upper-and lower-case labels for certain letters.', 'methods_required': ['Neural networks', 'Adam optimizer', 'ReLU activation function', 'Cross-entropy error function', 'Dropout', 'L1Penalty', 'L2Penalty', 'Label smoothing', 'L1L2MixPenalty', 'Custom Activation Layer'], 'description_short': 'This coursework studies the classification of handwritten digits using neural networks on the EMNIST Balanced dataset. The first part involves identifying and discussing overfitting problems in machine learning, then investigating these problems in wider and deeper neural networks. The second part requires implementing different methods to combat identified problems and comparing them both empirically and theoretically. The final part involves presenting conclusions and contextualizing them in the literature.', 'evaluation_metrics': ['Accuracy', 'Error curves', 'Validation performance'], 'submission_requirements': ['Submit online on the Learn course webpage', 'Include one zip file Sxxxxxx.zip containing test outputs, completed report as PDF, and local version of mlp code', 'Use the provided LaTeX template for the report', 'Do not submit dataset files or log files', 'Follow specific file naming conventions (Sxxxxxx_report.pdf, etc.)']}, 'created_at': '2025-11-25T00:53:04.620582+00:00', 'updated_at': None, 'deadline': '2026-01-14T00:00:00+00:00'}]]
