 foreachlayeronauniquetestvectorgeneratedusingyourstudentIDnumber.'}, {'id': '7c51844a-4406-48cf-82ff-d0966ac5ae3a', 'task': 'Implement the label smoothing function in EMNISTDataProvider and set α to 0.1.', 'source_sentence': '5. Toimplementthelabelsmoothingfunction,fillinlabel_smoothingfunctioninEMNISTDataProvider classof data_providers.pyandidentifywhenthisfunctioniscalled. Thisfunctionmustreplacethe hardtarget0labelsand1labelswith α and1−αrespectively. αmustbesetto0.1.'}, {'id': '7bef8fd9-f2cd-49e9-9a2c-d216d98674b0', 'task': 'Implement the L1 and L2 combined weight penalty as L1L2MixPenalty.', 'source_sentence': '6. Implement your proposed L1 and L2 combined weight penalty, as the L1L2MixPenalty in the mlp.penalties module.'}, {'id': 'f6cc5f45-dc3f-476a-88ea-0a24b61eb5ec', 'task': 'Conduct EMNIST experiments modifying the baseline network to use DropoutLayer, L1Penalty, or L2Penalty, and include an experiment with labelsmoothing only.', 'source_sentence': 'EMNIST Experiments. In this section you should modify your baseline network to one that uses DropoutLayer,L1Penalty,orL2Penaltyandtrainamodelforeachcase. Youwillalsorunoneexperiment withthebaselinesetuppluslabelsmoothing,usingnootherregularization techniques.'}, {'id': '256c5d89-d64d-4948-b357-6ad315313708', 'task': 'Specify the allowed hyperparameter ranges for Dropout inclusion probability and weight penalties.', 'source_sentence': 'TheDropoutinclusionprobabilityisafloatvalueintherange(0,1),e.g. 0.5,chosenmanually. Penaltycoefficient isalsoamanuallyselectedfloatvalue,e.g. 0.001,usuallyintherangeof0.1−0.00001.'}, {'id': 'eb7eef9f-7624-4edf-875f-8393d3037ea8', 'task': 'Select a set of four hyperparameter combinations for combined L1 and L2 experiments and justify the choices.', 'source_sentence': 'Therearemanyvalidcombinationsofexperimentstotry,butyoushouldmotivateyourspecificselection.'}], 'datasets': [{'name': 'EMNIST Balanced dataset', 'details': 'Extended MNIST-based dataset including handwritten digits and letters; 47-label reduced set; 28x28 images'}], 'deadline': '2025-11-21T12:00:00', 'weighting': '50%', 'deliverables': [{'name': 'Regularization test outputs', 'details': 'xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy generated by generate_regularization_layer_test_outputs.py'}, {'name': 'Coursework report (PDF)', 'details': 'Sxxxxxx_report.pdf submitted in the zip package'}, {'name': 'MLP code and Coursework_1 notebook', 'details': 'local mlp code including changes (.py files) and Coursework_1.ipynb'}, {'name': 'Submission ZIP file', 'details': 'Sxxxxxx.zip containing the above items (test outputs, report, code, Coursework_1.ipynb)'}], 'description_long': None, 'methods_required': ['DropoutLayer', 'L1Penalty', 'L2Penalty', 'L1L2MixPenalty', 'EMNISTDataProvider label_smoothing function'], 'description_short': 'Coursework2 focuses on classifying handwritten digit and letter images using neural networks with EMNIST Balanced dataset. It examines a fundamental ML problem (overfitting) and explores network width/depth variations. It requires implementing regularization techniques (Dropout, L1/L2 penalties, label smoothing) and a custom activation layer, and comparing approaches. The structure is divided into three tasks with empirical and theoretical evaluation. The main deliverable is a report, plus the code changes and test artifacts submitted as specified.', 'evaluation_metrics': ['Validation accuracy', 'Training/validation error curves', 'Test accuracy'], 'submission_requirements': ['Submit your completed report as a PDF file named Sxxxxxx_report.pdf', 'Submit one zip file Sxxxxxx.zip containing: xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy, Sxxxxxx_report.pdf, local mlp code (.py files) and Coursework_1.ipynb']}, 'created_at': '2025-11-25T12:04:45.808781+00:00', 'updated_at': None, 'deadline': '2026-01-14T00:00:00+00:00'}]]
