ed activation)', 'Adam optimizer'], 'description_short': 'Machine Learning Practical 2025/26 Coursework 2 focuses on classifying handwritten digits using EMNIST Balanced. The course explores network width and depth, and compares methods to tackle overfitting. It consists of three tasks: problem identification, regularization-based mitigations, and summarised conclusions contextualised by literature. Students implement neural network components (Dropout, penalties, label smoothing, custom activation) and run experiments to evaluate performance.', 'evaluation_metrics': ['Training error curves', 'Validation error curves', 'Training accuracy curves', 'Validation accuracy curves', 'Test performance on EMNIST Balanced dataset'], 'submission_requirements': ['Submit one zip file named Sxxxxxx.zip containing: xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy, Sxxxxxx_report.pdf, your local mlp code (including changed .py files), and Coursework_1.ipynb notebook.']}, 'created_at': '2025-11-26T11:25:06.657439+00:00', 'updated_at': None, 'deadline': '2026-01-14T00:00:00+00:00'}]]
