 conclusions.'}, {'id': '7f547e95-11c8-4e21-8f43-96a099f64988', 'task': '1 IdentificationofafundamentalprobleminmachinelearningasshowninFig1andsettingupabaseline systemonEMNISTbyavalidhyper-parametersearch.', 'duration': 1.0, 'source_sentence': '1 IdentificationofafundamentalprobleminmachinelearningasshowninFig1andsettingupabaseline systemonEMNISTbyavalidhyper-parametersearch.'}, {'id': 'f0341bd7-dfff-4367-998e-cca37ac8c970', 'task': 'Varyingnumberofhiddenunits. Initiallyyouwilltrainvarious1-hiddenlayernetworksbyusingeither32,64and128ReLUhiddenunitsperlayeronEMNIST.Notethat1-hiddenlayernetworkcontainstwolayers,one mappinginputunitstohiddenunitsandanotheronemappinghiddenunitstooutputunits. 2and3-hiddenlayernetworkswouldcontain3and4layersrespectively. MakesureyouuseAdamoptimiserwiththehyperparameters providedinthetemplateandtraineachnetworkfor100epochs.', 'duration': 1.0, 'source_sentence': 'Varyingnumberofhiddenunits. Initiallyyouwilltrainvarious1-hiddenlayernetworksbyusingeither32,64and128ReLUhiddenunitsperlayeronEMNIST.Notethat1-hiddenlayernetworkcontainstwolayers,one mappinginputunitstohiddenunitsandanotheronemappinghiddenunitstooutputunits. 2and3-hiddenlayer networkswouldcontain3and4layersrespectively. MakesureyouuseAdamoptimiserwiththehyperparameters providedinthetemplateandtraineachnetworkfor100epochs.'}, {'id': '9a72455e-910d-465c-9c33-b651bde4c26d', 'task': 'Varyingnumberoflayers. Hereyouwilltrainvariousneuralnetworksbyusingeither1,2,3hiddenlayerswith128ReLUhiddenunitsperlayeronEMNIST.MakesurethatyouuseAdamoptimiserwiththehyperparameters providedinthetemplateandtraineachnetworkfor100epochs.', 'duration': 1.0, 'source_sentence': 'Varyingnumberoflayers. Hereyouwilltrainvariousneuralnetworksbyusingeither1,2,3hiddenlayerswith128ReLUhiddenunitsperlayeronEMNIST.MakesurethatyouuseAdamoptimiserwiththehyperparameters providedinthetemplateandtraineachnetworkfor100epochs.'}, {'id': 'e7d82a20-ca17-4b38-a1fd-2e3f1fa162a3', 'task': 'DefinitionandMotivation. Weprovide theanalysisandexplanationforDropout,L1Penalty,L2Penalty,and labelsmoothinginthetemplatedocument,alongwithrelevantcitations.', 'duration': 0.75, 'source_sentence': 'DefinitionandMotivation. WeprovidetheanalysisandexplanationforDropout,L1Penalty,L2Penalty,andlabelsmoothinginthetemplatedocument,alongwithrelevantcitations.'}, {'id': 'fdb005bc-682e-440c-8ddf-1c20053e2e75', 'task': 'Implementing Dropout, Weight Penalty, Label Smoothing. Here you will implement DropoutLayer, L1PenaltyandL2Penaltyandtesttheircorrectness.', 'duration': 0.75, 'source_sentence': 'Implementing Dropout, Weight Penalty, Label Smoothing. Here you will implement DropoutLayer, L1PenaltyandL2Penaltyandtesttheircorrectness.'}, {'id': '8e972e24-f67f-4145-9526-e3b410f421c5', 'task': '1. ImplementtheDropoutclassintheDropoutLayerofthemlp.layersmodule. Youneedtoimplementfpropandbpropmethodsforthisclass.', 'duration': 0.75, 'source_sentence': '1. ImplementtheDropoutclassintheDropoutLayerofthemlp.layersmodule. Youneedtoimplementfpropandbpropmethodsforthisclass.'}, {'id': 'b0b80ab4-130d-483b-b0f3-58b12b89f9e9', 'task': '2. ImplementtheL1PenaltyandL2PenaltyclassintheL1PenaltyandL2Penaltyofthemlp.penalties module. Youneedtoimplement__call__andgradmethodsforthisclass.', 'duration': 0.75, 'source_sentence': '2. ImplementtheL1PenaltyandL2PenaltyclassintheL1PenaltyandL2Penaltyofthemlp.penalties module. Youneedtoimplement__call__andgradmethodsforthisclass.'}, {'id': '6b3a2088-34ea-47db-a174-4b821793cae4', 'task': '3. Verifythecorrectnessofyourimplementationusingthesuppliedunittestsin DropoutandPenalty_tests.ipynb', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': '3. Verifythecorrectnessofyourimplementationusingthesuppliedunittestsin DropoutandPenalty_tests.ipynb'}, {'id': 'aa563818-611d-4d15-b9e2-e4325f236d38', 'task': '4. Automaticallycreatetestoutputsxxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy,byrunningtheprovidedprogramscripts/generate_regularization_layer_test_outputs.pywhichusesyourcodefor thepreviously mentionedlayerstorunyourfprop,bprop,__call__andgradmethodswherenecessary foreachlayeronauniquetestvectorgeneratedusingyourstudentIDnumber.', 'duration': 1.0, 'source_sentence': '4. Automaticallycreatetestoutputsxxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy,byrunningtheprovidedprogramscripts/generate_regularization_layer_test_outputs.pywhichusesyourcodefor thepreviously mentionedlayerstorunyourfprop,bprop,__call__andgradmethodswherenecessary foreachlayeronauniquetestvectorgeneratedusingyourstudentIDnumber.'}, {'id': 'c8b58af9-e8d8-436d-b1ab-9218cb7e72b1', 'task': 'Toimplementthelabelsmoothingfunction,fillinlabel_smoothingfunctioninEMNISTDataProvider classof data_providers.pyandidentifywhenthisfunctioniscalled.', 'duration': 0.75, 'source_sentence': '5. Toimplementthelabelsmoothingfunction,fillinlabel_smoothingfunctioninEMNISTDataProvider classof data_providers.pyandidentifywhenthisfunctioniscalled.'}, {'id': '709116a5-96bd-425e-99a3-c2b8fa4dde90', 'task': 'Thisfunctionmustreplacethe hardtarget0labelsand1labelswith α and1−α respectively. αmustbesetto0.1.', 'duration': 0.25, 'source_sentence': 'Thisfunctionmustreplacethe hardtarget0labelsand1labelswith α and1−α respectively. αmustbesetto0.1.'}, {'id': 'a3a41fe5-9ea9-43a6-a122-b18b472adf9c', 'task': '6. Implement your proposed L1 and L2 combined weight penalty, as the L1L2MixPenalty in the mlp.penaltiesmodule.', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': '6. Implement your proposed L1 and L2 combined weight penalty, as the L1L2MixPenalty in the mlp.penaltiesmodule.'}, {'id': 'b2021278-cf96-4adf-b499-ed04ed62ab4d', 'task': 'EMNIST Experiments. In this section you should modify your baseline network to one that uses DropoutLayer,L1Penalty,orL2Penaltyandtrainamodelforeachcase.', 'duration': 1.0, 'source_sentence': 'EMNIST Experiments. In this section you should modify your baseline network to one that uses DropoutLayer,L1Penalty,orL2Penaltyandtrainamodelforeachcase.'}, {'id': '57d8c7db-e088-4374-89a1-1cd50eefb8ab', 'task': 'The Dropoutinclusionprobability is a float value in the range (0,1), e.g. 0.5, chosen manually. Penalty coefficient is also a manually selected float value, e.g. 0.001, usually in the range of0.1−0.00001.', 'duration': 0.75, 'source_sentence': 'The Dropoutinclusionprobability is a float value in the range (0,1), e.g. 0.5, chosen manually. Penalty coefficient is also a manually selected float value, e.g. 0.001, usually in the rangeof0.1−0.00001.'}, {'id': '17791036-5ae9-4dd8-8a6d-5c2a578105fa', 'task': 'You should identifyandargueforasetof4differenthyperparametercombinationsforwhichyouwillrunthecombinedL1andL2experiments.', 'duration': 0.75, 'source_sentence': 'You should identifyandargueforasetof4differenthyperparametercombinationsforwhichyouwillrunthecombinedL1andL2experiments.'}, {'id': '59f14182-08f1-48e6-9b04-c950ead152e9', 'task': 'You should run the labelsmoothing experiment without other regularization techniques.', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': 'You should run the labelsmoothing experiment without other regularization techniques.'}, {'id': '80e78262-ec17-42cc-8fc9-2a63c3a42d1d', 'task': 'You will finally investigate and explain the performance problems with a provided model setup and experiment run, that uses a custom activation layer.', 'duration': 0.75, 'source_sentence': 'You will finally investigate and explain the performance problems with a provided model setup and experiment run, that uses a custom activation layer.'}, {'id': '4a1e57ec-d9cd-4e4b-9d9b-50e33cfb89ce', 'task': 'The questions in mlp-cw1-questions.tex that you must answer and count for this task are: QuestionTable3;QuestionFigure4;QuestionTable4;QuestionFigure5;QuestionFigure6;Question7;Question8;Question9.', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': 'The questions in mlp-cw1-questions.tex that you must answer and count for this task are: QuestionTable3;QuestionFigure4;QuestionTable4;QuestionFigure5;QuestionFigure6;Question7;Question8;Question9.'}], 'datasets': [{'name': 'EMNIST Balanced dataset', 'details': 'Extended MNIST Balanced dataset used for coursework; 28×28 centred images; 62 potential classes but 47 labels are used after merging certain upper/lowercase letters; training set about twice the MNIST training set.'}], 'deadline': '2025-11-21', 'weighting': None, 'deliverables': [{'name': 'Coursework report', 'details': 'Completed report as a PDF file using the provided template.'}, {'name': 'MLP coursework code', 'details': 'Local version of the mlp code including any changes you made to the modules (.py files).'}, {'name': ' Coursework_1.ipynb', 'details': 'Notebook with experiment setup and related content.'}, {'name': 'Regularization test pack', 'details': 'xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy generated from tests.'}, {'name': 'Submission zip', 'details': 'A zip file named Sxxxxxx.zip containing the test pack, report, code, and Coursework_1.ipynb.'}], 'description_long': None, 'methods_required': ['Adam optimizer', 'DropoutLayer', 'L1Penalty', 'L2Penalty', 'L1L2MixPenalty', 'EMNISTDataProvider (with label smoothing)', 'Custom Activation Layer'], 'description_short': 'The coursework focuses on classifying handwritten digits using neural networks on an extended EMNIST Balanced dataset. It analyzes overfitting and regularization (Dropout, L1/L2 penalties, label smoothing) and experiments with a custom activation layer. It uses a three-task structure: problem identification, regularization evaluation, and conclusions. Students implement new layers and penalties, run experiments, and submit a report and code.', 'evaluation_metrics': ['training error', 'validation error', 'training accuracy', 'validation accuracy'], 'submission_requirements': ['Your coursework submissions should include one zip file Sxxxxxx.zip that should contain your test outputs xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy, your completed report as Sxxxxxx_report.pdf, your local version of the mlp code including any changes you madetothemodules (.pyfiles) and the Coursework_1.ipynb notebook.']}, 'created_at': '2025-11-30T10:30:50.494333+00:00', 'updated_at': None, 'deadline': '2025-12-31T00:00:00+00:00'}]]
