lasses.'}, {'id': '75db2024-99db-4899-9da0-851be0ddb5af', 'task': 'Train 1-hidden-layer networks on EMNIST using 32, 64 and 128 ReLU hidden units per layer as the varying hidden-units experiment.', 'duration': 2.0, 'source_sentence': 'Varyingnumberofhiddenunits. Initiallyyouwilltrainvarious1-hiddenlayernetworksbyusingeither32,64 and128ReLUhiddenunitsperlayeronEMNIST.'}, {'id': '056e1a35-5ad8-4afd-a313-4a66112319b5', 'task': 'Use the Adam optimiser with the hyperparameters provided in the template and train each network for 100 epochs for the above experiments.', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': 'MakesureyouuseAdamoptimiserwiththehyperparameters providedinthetemplateandtraineachnetworkfor100epochs.'}, {'id': '75fc98d6-2a0e-49ab-8e25-1ab44114703a', 'task': 'Train networks with 1, 2, and 3 hidden layers using 128 ReLU hidden units per layer as the varying-layers experiment.', 'duration': 2.0, 'source_sentence': 'Varyingnumberoflayers. Hereyouwilltrainvariousneuralnetworksbyusingeither1,2,3hiddenlayerswith 128ReLUhiddenunitsperlayeronEMNIST.'}, {'id': '579b3828-787a-4be6-a89f-05a80a8196ee', 'task': 'Visualise and discuss how increasing the number of hidden units affects validation performance and whether it worsens or mitigates overfitting.', 'duration': 1.0, 'source_sentence': 'Visualiseanddiscusshowincreasingnumberof hiddenunitsaffectsthevalidationperformanceandwhetheritworsensormitigatestheoverfittingproblem.'}, {'id': 'da3d6780-0c37-489b-82e2-d7b8c3355b2f', 'task': 'Visualise and discuss how increasing the number of layers affects validation performance and whether it worsens or mitigates overfitting.', 'duration': 1.0, 'source_sentence': 'Visualiseanddiscusshowincreasingnumberof layersaffectsthevalidationperformanceandwhetheritworsensormitigatestheoverfittingproblem.'}, {'id': 'befdc6ad-cdb7-4ecd-aa7a-79a7461619ce', 'task': 'Modify the baseline network to use DropoutLayer, L1Penalty, or L2Penalty and train a model for each case as specified.', 'duration': 2.0, 'source_sentence': 'In this section you should modify your baseline network to one that uses DropoutLayer,L1Penalty,orL2Penaltyandtrainamodelforeachcase.'}, {'id': 'f331a3f4-a9e4-4468-8b6a-cf5fa9ec7dd0', 'task': 'Run one experiment with the baseline setup plus label smoothing only (no other regularization).', 'duration': 1.0, 'source_sentence': 'You will alsorunoneexperiment withthebaselinesetuppluslabelsmoothing,usingnootherregularizationtechniques.'}, {'id': '3188eee2-3ddf-4758-aca7-c71f458f326a', 'task': 'Use a baseline network containing 3 hidden layers and 128 hidden units with ReLU activation for the EMNIST experiments.', 'duration': 0.1, 'source_sentence': 'For the experiments,your baseline network should contain 3 hidden layers and 128 hidden units with ReLU activation function.'}, {'id': '5ea30b4d-59e1-4703-9c7d-26989cde881e', 'task': 'Use the Adam optimiser with learning rate 10^-4 for the baseline and regularisation experiments as specified in the template.', 'duration': 0.1, 'source_sentence': 'You shouldusetheAdamoptimiserwithalearningrateof10−4 asspecifiedinthetemplate.'}, {'id': '9c998cd1-3b69-455f-8d43-9831cec9f08f', 'task': 'Investigate whether/how Dropout, L1/L2 penalties, and label smoothing address the overfitting problem, and study generalisation performance for each.', 'duration': 2.0, 'source_sentence': 'Yourmainaimistoi)investigatewhether/howeachofthesefunctionsaddressestheabovementionedproblem, ii)studythegeneralisationperformanceofyournetworkwhenusedwithoneofthesefunctions,iii)discoverthe bestpossiblenetworkconfiguration,whentheonlyavailableoptionstochoosefromareDropoutandWeight Penaltyfunctionsandthehyper-parameters(DropoutinclusionprobabilityandpenaltycoefficientfortheWeight Penaltyfunctions).'}, {'id': '7ef38b63-ad4f-4105-8440-b591309a7067', 'task': 'Apply weight penalty to both weights and biases of your layers when using L1/L2 penalties.', 'duration': 0.25, 'source_sentence': 'Youshoulduseweightpenaltyonbothweightsandbiasesofyourlayers.'}, {'id': 'db437c17-0116-4348-9a35-946abcd0c7f9', 'task': 'Use the prespecified hyperparameter values from Table 3 of the template for L1/L2 regularisation and Dropout experiments where provided.', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': 'We have prespecified for what hyperparameter values you should run each individual experiment for L1/L2 regularisation and Dropout on Table 3 of the template.'}, {'id': '7cb19fe8-b274-467f-9980-91a19678d38b', 'task': 'Identify and justify a set of 4 different hyperparameter combinations to run for your combined L1 and L2 experiments and run those experiments.', 'duration': 1.5, 'source_sentence': 'Youwillhavetoidentifyandargueforasetof4differenthyperparametercombinationsforwhichyouwillrun thecombinedL1andL2experiments(foryourimplementation).'}, {'id': '4fe64038-37c7-4672-b2f6-612a8605cb27', 'task': 'Run the label smoothing experiment without other regularization techniques.', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': 'Youshouldrunthelabelsmoothingexperimentwithoutotherregularizationtechniques.'}, {'id': '1343702d-e7db-4e85-b7e9-7ca0782194e8', 'task': 'Investigate and explain performance problems with the provided model setup that uses a custom activation layer.', 'duration': 1.5, 'source_sentence': 'Youwillfinallyinvestigateandexplaintheperformanceproblemswithaprovidedmodelsetupandexperiment run,thatusesacustomactivationlayer.'}, {'id': '428633d0-a506-4064-b8c6-e9a89c207448', 'task': 'Copy the LaTeX template and style files from coursework1/report into the directory that will contain your report.', 'duration': 0.25, 'source_sentence': 'AdirectorycalledreportwhichcontainstheLaTeXtemplateandstylefilesforyourreport. Youshould copyallthesefilesintothedirectorywhichwillcontainyourreport.'}, {'id': '078446f3-89eb-4d66-a8be-5e0d5077d409', 'task': 'Add your Student Number in place of (SXXXXXX) at the start of mlp-cw1-questions.tex before inputting answers.', 'duration': 0.1, 'source_sentence': 'Whileinputtingyouranswersin(mlp-cw1-questions.tex),thefirstthingyoushoulddoisaddyourStudent Numberinplaceof(SXXXXXX)atthestartofthefile.'}, {'id': '0b3a39bb-5561-40c1-b900-3de4e4d56b8f', 'task': 'Edit mlp-cw1-questions.tex to answer each question, only editing the text inside the \\youranswer brackets.', 'duration': 2.0, 'source_sentence': 'Then,answereachquestion,beingcarefultoonlyeditthetextthatappearsinthebracketsofthecommands(\\youranswer).'}, {'id': 'b72282c1-91b4-43cb-ae77-98a635e1860b', 'task': 'Include figures as vector graphics in the report (instead of raster images) so plot details remain visible.', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': 'Ideally,allfiguresshouldbeincludedinyourreportfileasvectorgraphicsfilesratherthanrasterfilesasthis willmakesurealldetailintheplotisvisible.'}, {'id': 'cf1b6329-a60c-46c4-83e5-e8f8f14c4695', 'task': 'Create the report PDF from the LaTeX source by running pdflatex, bibtex, and pdflatex multiple times as instructed.', 'duration': 0.5, 'source_sentence': 'Tocreateapdffilemlp-cw1-template.pdffromaLaTeXsourcefile(mlp-cw1-template.tex),youcan runthefollowinginaterminal: pdflatex mlp-cw1-template bibtex mlp-cw1-template pdflatex mlp-cw1-template pdflatex mlp-cw1-template'}, {'id': '67ffcb6d-92f1-45ec-8453-58ea44237317', 'task': 'Create the submission zip using the recommended zip command and your student number in the filename.', 'duration': 0.25, 'source_sentence': 'YoucanusethiscommandonLinuxmachinestozipallthefilestogether– zip -r Sxxxxxx.zip mlp/ Coursework_1.ipynb Sxxxxxx_report.pdf xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy'}, {'id': '9acc994a-5967-4ca5-b250-07e9e42c691f', 'task': 'Check the contents of your zip file using unzip -l Sxxxxxx.zip to ensure required files are included.', 'duration': 0.1, 'source_sentence': 'Pleasecheckwhetherthesefilesareincludedinthezipfilebeforemovingtothenextstep: unzip -l Sxxxxxx.zip'}, {'id': 'b720434a-2c02-4883-8d60-b2b2541d40d4', 'task': 'Ensure the zip file does not include model weights and is only a few MB in size.', 'duration': 0.1, 'source_sentence': 'NotethatthisfilemustnothaveyourmodelweightsanditssizeshouldbefewMbsonly.'}, {'id': 'c6395bcc-5133-4c62-87ea-317711216a73', 'task': 'Log in to the Learn Machine Learning Practical (2025-2026) webpage and upload your Sxxxxxx.zip submission using the SubmitCoursework1Here attachment workflow.', 'duration': 0.25, 'source_sentence': 'Once you have successfully created the .zip file and checked its content, you need to login to your Learn Machine Learning Practical (2025-2026)[YR]webpageandsubmitthefile.'}, {'id': 'bbf3340b-3177-4415-8074-a85097674e50', 'task': 'Final check: ensure your zip file is not empty and not missing files before final submission.', 'duration': 0.25, 'source_sentence': 'Pleasecheckthatyourzipfileisnotemptyor missingfiles.'}], 'datasets': [{'name': 'EMNIST Balanced', 'details': 'Extended MNIST Balanced dataset (from NIST Special Database 19), images 28x28, reduced label set of 47 labels where some upper/lowercase merged; training set has about twice the number of examples as MNIST.'}], 'deadline': '2025-11-21T12:00:00', 'weighting': 'This assignment will be assessed out of 100 marks and forms 50% of your final grade for the course.', 'deliverables': [{'name': 'Sxxxxxx_report.pdf', 'details': 'Completed report PDF generated from provided LaTeX template and containing answers to mlp-cw1-questions.tex; file must be renamed using your student number.'}, {'name': 'xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy', 'details': 'Automatically generated test outputs file created by running scripts/generate_regularization_layer_test_outputs.py --student_id Sxxxxxx; to be included in submission zip.'}, {'name': 'local mlp code (.py files) and Coursework_1.ipynb', 'details': 'Your local modified mlp code including any changes to provided .py files and the Coursework_1.ipynb notebook must be included in the submission zip.'}, {'name': 'Sxxxxxx.zip', 'details': 'One zip file containing mlp/ Coursework_1.ipynb Sxxxxxx_report.pdf and xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy; must not include model weights and should be a few MB only.'}], 'description_long': 'The coursework uses the EMNIST Balanced dataset (47 labels, 28x28 images) and the mlp2025-26/coursework1 branch of the course Github repository. Tasks: (1) identify and discuss overfitting shown in provided training/validation curves and run baseline hyper-parameter experiments, (2) implement DropoutLayer, L1Penalty, L2Penalty, a proposed L1L2MixPenalty, and label smoothing; test and run experiments to evaluate how these methods affect generalisation and performance (including experiments with a provided CustomActivation layer), and (3) produce a structured report using the provided LaTeX template and submit the report PDF, code, and generated regularization test outputs in a named zip file.', 'methods_required': ['Neural networks (multilayer perceptrons) with ReLU activation', 'Adam optimiser (use hyperparameters provided in template)', 'Cross-entropy error function', 'Dropout (original formulation with scaling by inclusion probability)', 'L1 weight penalty', 'L2 weight penalty', 'Combined L1 and L2 weight penalty (L1L2MixPenalty)', 'Label smoothing (alpha = 0.1)', 'Custom activation function (investigate performance problems)', 'Validation-based model selection (use validation performance to pick best model)'], 'description_short': 'This coursework studies classification of images of handwritten digits/letters using neural networks on the EMNIST Balanced dataset. You must identify an overfitting problem from training/validation curves, set up a baseline with hyper-parameter search, and investigate mitigation methods including Dropout, L1/L2 weight penalties, a combined L1/L2 penalty, and label smoothing. You will run experiments using the provided code repository branch, implement required layers and penalties, test them, and submit a PDF report plus code and generated test outputs.', 'evaluation_metrics': ['Training and validation error (cross-entropy) curves', 'Training and validation accuracy curves', 'Validation performance (used for model selection)', 'Test performance (report test performance of best model)'], 'submission_requirements': ['Submit one zip file named Sxxxxxx.zip containing mlp/ Coursework_1.ipynb Sxxxxxx_report.pdf and xxxxxx_regularization_test_pack.npy', 'Report must be submitted as a PDF file named Sxxxxxx_report.pdf generated from the provided LaTeX template (mlp-cw1-template.tex); edit mlp-cw1-questions.tex to add answers', 'Include only the local mlp code (.py files), Coursework_1.ipynb, report PDF, and the regularization test pack .npy file; do not submit model weights or dataset files', 'Use the provided LaTeX template and include figures (ideally as vector graphics) and bibtex references in ref.bib', 'Check zip contents with unzip -l Sxxxxxx.zip before upload', 'Upload the zip file on the Learn Machine Learning Practical (2025-2026) webpage under SubmitCoursework1Here']}, 'created_at': '2025-11-30T10:35:36.844944+00:00', 'updated_at': None, 'deadline': '2026-01-09T00:00:00+00:00'}]]
